<br>
Also, after the chanter starts mezzing, i'll hit them with both spells and snare.  This is so that the mobs will come after me when mez breaks and the chanter can remez without having to channel.  I have better AC and more HP than my level 53 enchanter friend, and will ultimately take less damage cause she'll get the mez off sooner.  <br>
<br>
Of course, this is all making sure I'm not the main healer.   But, when not on a raid, aggro doens't hurt as much as some druids think and compentent groupmates know how to recover.  I also have a deal with my cleric friend not to heal me unless I look like I'm in real danger.  The last time I died was when i rooted myself fighting a green wurm.  <br>
<br>
And, of course, I'm only level 51.  I suppose that damage at higher levels would be insupportable later, but not getting the damage increase from Fixation of Ro is too much to lose by waiting until 50% <p>Ray,<BR>
